Let them sleep in!

Have you ever wondered why kids are so tired after school? In my opinion I think it is because they have to get up so early. Some adults cant even manage to roll out of bed at six in the morning, let alone a kid. We expect children to get up super early and make it with no naps till nine or ten o'clock at night and then repeat.How about letting them sleep in a little later and start school at ten in the morning and go till four in the afternoon?
I bet you are wondering how that would affect a persons daily life by switching to this schedule. First by allowing children to wake up on their own time clock the children would be able to cut out certain unless vitamins such as Melatonin. Melatonin is used to help children and adults find their normal sleep routine or alter it around. Which sounds better to you? The second way this would affect the childs life is by allowing them to actually wake up and not need coffee or tea or soething sugary to boost them. In  the long run its just a great idea. The thrid way doesnt sound so great because yes it would be a big change in everyones schedules. Some people would have to change around schedules to work in a sitter whereas others by save by not needing a sitter.
All around this is a great idea and has been mentioned so many times that it has encouraged the school systems to switch to four day school weeks. Other school systems have turned to block scheduling instead of normal days to help their students in their daily lives. So why wouldn't you want to help your child by voting yes for a shorter school day that allows them to sleep in?
